Program: Outlook
Title: After Malala Yousafzai: Life for girls in Swat
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p015zlj3
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 28 Mar 2013
Matthew Bannister talks to Pakistani politician Nadia Sher Khan about the challenges facing girls and women in Swat. We also hear from two groups of students - one in Mingora, home of Malala Yousafzai, and one from Robert Clack school near London - about the impact of the attack on Malala last October. And Sierra Leonean student Alpha Bangura tells us about the responsibility he feels towards his family having won a scholarship to Morocco. Picture: Matthew Bannister, Outlook Presenter Show less